http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/SIT-urged-to-file-criminal-case-against-Prestige-Estates/article13996207.ece

Samaj Parivartana Samudaya founder-president S.R. Hiremath has urged the Special Investigation Team probing into the scandal in the office of the Lokayukta to file a criminal case against Prestige Estates and Projects Limited for exerting pressure on a public servant of the grade of Principal Secretary.In a letter to the Additional Director-General of Police (ADGP) and SIT head, Mr. Hiremath said that the statements of Basavaraju, Principal Secretary, Revenue, recorded by the SIT clearly implicates Prestige Estates and Projects Limited in trying to influence Mr. Basavaraju through the principal accused in the Lokayukta scandal Y. Ashwin for sanctioning five acres of government land in Devanahalli in Bengaluru Rural district for the Prestige-Golfshire project.